tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a comprehensive visual redesign,
  including a new sleep-themed color palette, enhanced form layouts, polished UI
  components, and consistent styling across all sections, transforming the app's
  look and feel.
overview: "The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. I began by analyzing the
  existing design, identifying areas like the color palette, typography,
  spacing, and form elements as needing significant improvement. My approach
  involved a multi-step redesign: first, I introduced a calming, sleep-themed
  color palette and custom utility classes. Then, I revamped the main
  questionnaire form, adding subtle background elements and a more engaging
  progress bar. The intro section was transformed with a hero element and
  feature cards, replacing simple bullet points. Key UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders received a polished update with
  improved visual feedback. Crucially, I ensured consistent styling by updating
  all questionnaire sections to use a new card-style grouping, moving away from
  plain gray boxes. Finally, the report section was also updated to align with
  the new theme, featuring consistent gradient headers and refined content
  presentation. The overall outcome is a more professional, visually appealing,
  and cohesive application that better reflects its purpose as a sleep health
  assessment tool."
